items.text:
POWERHOUSE CASTING is looking for real people (Ages 18+) to participate in a paid conversation project.  

Seeking Real People Having Real Conversations.

Get Paid to Chat With a Friend – Each Individual will be paid $35 USD per Hour 
 
We’re partnering with a technology research company that is studying how people naturally speak, react, and interact in everyday conversation. The goal is to help improve how future digital tools understand real human communication.
 
What’s involved?
• A one-hour+ Zoom conversation with a friend
• Casual, unscripted, natural discussion
• You can participate for up to 5 hours total
• Paid $35 USD per hour per person ($48 CAD).  
*Direct payment to you as long as you follow the criterion.
That means you and your friend could each earn up to $175 USD (All Inclusive) for simply having real conversations.
 
Who we’re looking for:
• Friends who are comfortable on camera
• All ages 18+
• All backgrounds, and lived experiences welcome
• Natural, expressive communicators

No acting is required. No memorizing lines. Just real people being themselves having a conversation.
This is a straightforward, paid research opportunity conducted remotely from home.
 
VERY IMPORTANT NOTES TO KEEP IN MIND BEFORE RECORDING. MAKE SURE YOU DO THE FOLLOWING IN ORDER FOR YOUR FOOTAGE TO BE CONSIDERED 
 
EVERYONE MUST BE 18 YEARS OLD OR OLDER 
 
YOU MUST RECORD IN 1080p RESOLUTION OR HIGHER 
 
YOU MUST RECORD YOUR FOOTAGE USING A LAPTOP OR COMPUTER. DO NOT USE YOUR PHONE
 
DO NOT WEAR ANY FACIAL ACCESSORIES WHEN RECORDING (NO HATS, NO GLASSES ETC.)
 
YOU MUST HAVE MINIMAL OR NO FACIAL HAIR TO BE CONSIDERED. 
THEY NEED TO SEE YOUR UNOBSTRUCTED FACE AS CLEARLY AS POSSIBLE  
 
 
If you’re interested, please follow this link for more instructions 
 
LINK: 
https://velvet.video
Click "sign up". Once prompted for a code, use GXLO-86IL-ZTQ0

sharedPost.text:
Vancouver Casting Call

Friends, I am searching for someone to cast in a short, web video I am producing and wanted to widen my net. I am looking for a 50+ aged man from Manitoba with availability here in Vancouver BC (or nearby; Victoria, lower Mainland etc) for a single day between February 23 and 28th. I included some images and a video sample of the variety of folks I am looking for.

The Project: We are producing a short video for distribution on the internet. This isn't a high-pressure sales pitch; it’s a quiet, grounded reflection.

The Role: "The Manitoba Local"
Age: 50+ something year old male.
EDIT: Yes, this is a paid shoot. If you'd like, send me your preferred day rate as well. 

The Voice: This is the most critical element. We need a voice that is smooth, warm, and resonant. It should feel like a conversation over a morning coffee or a tailgate. No "announcer" voices—we want authentic, understated gravitas.

Look: Rustic, rural, blue-collar. We are looking for someone who looks like they’ve put in a hard day’s work—weathered skin, honest eyes, and a natural comfort in outdoor settings. Think "The Salt of the Earth." Calm, wise, and connected to Manitoba. We are open to being surprised and have our expectations challenged in the best way possible.

Key Requirements
Ability to deliver a monologue with emotional nuance without being overly dramatic.
A genuine Manitoba/Prairie sensibility is a must.

How to Apply
Please submit the following by email to tristan@vela-creative.com:
-A current headshot or clear photo (no filters, please—we want to see the "character" in your face).
-A brief video intro (60 seconds) telling us about your favorite spot in the province. Yes, you can do this on your phone.
-A voice sample or reel if available.

Note: We are prioritizing authenticity. If you’ve spent your life on the land or in a shop and have a voice like velvet, we want to hear from you—even if you don't have a traditional acting resume.

⚡️Need to create your first showreel / freshen up your old one?⚡️
Happy Sunday all!

I provide a very affordable showreel service for new or established actors/directors/cinematographers/comedians/hobbyists etc.

Basically, send me your footage (or I can try and source it for you online if it's commercially aired) and I shall edit it together into a lovely reel.

Please see samples of recent clients in the link below 😎

I'm an actor myself so I know how frustrating it can be, especially when you're starting out, to collate your footage together to get more work, without wanting to spend a fortune.

My rates are £20/hour, with duration of work depending on how much footage you have. The average reels have been around £80-£100 for my clients. Much more affordable than the companies that charge £250+ !!

For any further info / enquiries / to book my services, drop me an email and I'll respond as quickly as I can:

reelsforanyone@gmail.com

I'll look forward to hearing from you.

Thanks!

😎

www.youtube.com/@Reels.For.Anyone

items.text:
🎥 **CASTING CALL – Actor/Actress for a Training Video**

Hi there! 👋

At Panda Motion, we are looking for an actor or actress to play the role of a host/narrator in an approx. 25-minute cybersecurity training video series.

**Details:**

🎬 Project: Corporate training video (6-7 episodes, approx. 4 minutes each, 25 mins total) for an LMS platform

📍 Location: Kraków or surrounding area

📆 Date: 1 shooting day (late February / early March - TBD)

📲 Usage Rights: Unlimited time and territory (buyout)

💰 Rate: To be discussed

**Who are we looking for?**

✅ Male or Female, approx. 30-40 years old

✅ Fluent spoken English (C1/C2 level) - mandatory requirement

✅ Professional posture and trustworthy appearance (corporate look)

✅ Experience in public speaking and/or on-camera work

✅ Knowledge of cybersecurity topics is a plus

📩 Please send your applications to: casting@pandamotion.pl
Subject line: “Casting – LMS training”

**Please include in your application:**

Name, age, height, city of residence, and phone number

2–3 current photos (headshot + full body)

Demo/self-tape in English

A recording of a min. 30-second speech in English (any text - read or improvised)

Link to showreel/portfolio (if available)

A brief note about your acting experience

We look forward to receiving your applications! 😊✨

items.text:
Auditions
Waiting for the Parade
by John Murrell
Don't miss your chance to audition for Pivot Theatre's upcoming production of this Canadian classic!
The word 
Director:Kayt Roth
Producer:The Pivot Theatre Team
Audition Dates:
February 22, 2026 at 12:00 pm
February 23, 2026 at 7:00 pm
Audition Venue: 
Progress Lab 1422 (1422 William Street, Vancouver)
Audition Requirements: 
Auditions will be cold reads from the script
Production Dates: 
April 11 and 12, 2026

Show Venue: 
Progress Lab 1422 (1422 William Street, Vancouver)
Rehearsals:
First rehearsal Wednesday, February 25, 2026, then Tuesday and Thursday evenings and all day Saturdays beginning March 3, 2026.
Synopsis:          
On the home front in Calgary during World War II, five women deal with loneliness, infidelity, heartbreak, and friendship as they support the troops, the Red Cross, and each other. This play showcases the women who stayed behind, and focuses on the effect that the war has on them, their relationships, and their families.
Characters Required:
CATHERINE (F, late 20s to early 30s): Her husband is off fighting in Europe. Practical and easygoing, works against his wishes to make ends meet. Singing ability an asset.
JANET (F, mid to late 30s): Uptight. Thinks she’s in charge. Her husband was excluded from active duty, so she tries twice as hard to make up for it by managing every aspect of local war effort programs. Piano playing and singing ability an asset.
MARGARET (F, mid-40s to 50s): A widow. Religious. Exhausted, with no use for Janet. Worries constantly about dying running in her family, and about her two adult sons, a sailor and a Communist. Singing ability an asset.
EVE (F, 20s): A teacher. In love with screen star Leslie Howard, and unhappy with her much older husband. A naïve optimist who is stuck between a war that might last years and a husband eager to, but unable to fight. Throws herself into her work supporting the troops. Singing ability an asset.
MARTA (F, late 20s-early 30s): German-Canadian seamstress. Dealing with her father’s arrest as a Nazi sympathizer and being ostracized by the community. Singing ability an asset. German accent a must.
 
Notes:  
Auditions are on a first come, first served basis. Actors will be seen in the order they arrive.
Roles are open to everyone regardless of background, race, gender, orientation, or ability. We encourage everyone to audition as we will be casting whoever is best for the role.
Auditions will be cold readings from the script. Actors are encouraged to read the script on their own prior to auditioning. (Note: director will not provide copies of the script.)
Please bring a résumé and headshot to auditions
This is a NON-EQUITY, volunteer production
Please forward questions to hq@pivottheatre.ca.
 
See you there!
Your Pivot Theatre Team
Pivot Theatre
1422 William Street, Vancouver, BC
 facebook  instagram
To unsubscribe from these emails, please click here.
Unsubscribe
 Sent by MailerLite

🎬 Casting do projektu fabularnego (reel shortsy / platforma streamingowa)

Do adaptacji książki poszukujemy aktorów do ról młodzieżowych oraz dorosłych.

Szukamy:

• nastolatka– uczennica liceum, blondynka, delikatna, wyrazista emocjonalnie

• nastolatek– uczeń liceum, brunet, buntowniczy charakter, mile widziane widoczne tatuaże

• nastolatek - wysoki blondyn, uczen liceum

•  nastolatka- uczennica liceum o brązowych włosach, wyrazista wizualnie

• elegancka kobieta 40+ o ostrych rysach twarzy do roli matki

• mężczyzna do roli dyrektora szkoły

Zależy nam na naturalności, ekranowej charyzmie i wiarygodności.

📅 Casting: początek marca
🎥 Zdjęcia: kwiecień
📺 Emisja: social media + platforma streamingowa

Budżet w trakcie finalizacji – szczegóły przekażemy zainteresowanym i wstępnie zakwalifikowanym na casting osobom.

📩 Zgłoszenia prosimy wysyłać na:
impresariat.kamedstudio@gmail.com
W tytule maila proszę wpisać KSIĄŻKA

W treści maila prosimy o przesłanie:
• aktualnych zdjęć (twarz + sylwetka)
• miejsca zamieszkania
• wizytówki aktorskiej / showreelu (link do YouTube)

Na zgłoszenia czekamy do niedzieli 15.02.2026

❗️WSPÓŁPRACA KOMERCYJNA ❗️
Poszukuję trzech modeli (anatomicznych mężczyzn) do stałej współpracy w okresie od maja do lipca. 

👉Kontrahenci i ich produkty: 

C-in2 New York LLC - produkty: slipy, bokserki

Saligia LLC - produkty: bokserki, kąpielówki 

Sukrew UK LTD - produkty: kąpielówki, slipy

Skull&Bones - produkty: Slipy, bokserki, kąpielówki

👉Pracujemy wyłącznie w studiu we Wrocławiu (nie zwracam za dojazd i nie rozliczam biletów na przejazdy PKP i Flixbus) 

👉 Wymagania do wyboru modeli: 
* Widoczna muskulatura, 
* Brak tatuaży zawierających symbole religijne, przemoc i wulgaryzmy lub broń (w tym też broń białą)
* Naturalny kolor włosów
* Brak zarostu na klatce piersiowej i pod pachami 
* Obywatelstwo polskie, francuskie lub brytyjskie

👉 Stawki od 800 do 1100 złotych za sesję (przy minimum wykonania czterech sesji). Do tego osobno ustalana jest stawka za przekazanie praw wizerunkowych do działalności komercyjnej firm na okres minimum 3 lat. W trakcie trwania umowy model nie może we własnym zakresie korzystać tych zdjęć.

👉 Moje portfolio: 

https://panodbodypaintingu.pl/

https://www.instagram.com/pan_od_bodypaintingu/

items.text:
Hey folks, so here’s my little pitch, I suppose! I’d introduce myself, but the profile is right there;

Actually, scratch that, it feels weird starting without at least my first name. I’m Will! I’ve been a lifelong creative, attending several drama schools in my twenties and continuously writing scripts that I’ve often abandoned halfway through.

However, no longer! I set myself a goal this year of writing 6 short films, each with a different theme and genre, in an anthology style akin to Inside No. 9 or Black Mirror.

As a result, I’m very pleased to showcase the first finished screenplay with a short synopsis here and potentially cast the project as follows;

DISCLAIMER:

**THIS PROJECT CONTAINS VERY STRONG & MATURE THEMES NOT LIMITED TO BUT INCLUDING SEXUAL REFERENCES, PROFANITY & SELF-HARM. PLEASE ONLY APPLY IF YOU ARE 18+ AND ARE NOT SENSITIVE TO THIS MATERIAL. **
**(UNPAID OPPORTUNITY)**

**LOCATIONS: NORTH LIVERPOOL AREA.**

Synopsis:

A lonely thirty-something following a bad breakup stumbles across a group of paranormal investigators who have a very different take on what life after death could truly be, and what happens to an unfortunate few.

Casting Call:

**Director/Camera Operator: **I plan to film this project myself if necessary. Although I lack professional equipment, there will be scenes better handled by someone with more expertise in this area.

**Tex (20-30s Female):** Edgy and sarcastic with a sharp wit, charisma comes naturally to her with a goth/emo aesthetic.

**Scoob (20-30s Male): **A straight-talking rebel to the system, rocker/gothic aesthetic similar to Tex. Heavy smoker on the path to degeneracy.

**Pol (20-30s Female): **Academically astute yet magnetized toward those who follow unconventional paths, supportive and generally well-meaning.

**Rhys (20+ Male): **Through and through an objectivist, studying and research are his bread and butter. The archivist and quiet guide of the group, with an intellectually introverted disposition.

items.text:
CASTING CALL: THE COLLECTOR (Short Film)

Production: Independent Short Film

Genre: Supernatural Horror / Psychological Thriller

Location: York, England

Shoot Dates: April 12th and 13th

Compensation: Unpaid. Catering provided. This project is intended as the beginning of an ongoing creative collaboration.

Synopsis:

The Collector explores the predatory nature of darkness and the dangerous misunderstanding of vulnerability. Innocence is not seen as purity, but as something to be consumed.

Roles Available:

Grace (Female, 40s) Lead

A composed, intelligent professional with a quiet but formidable presence. Calm, controlled, and shaped by survival.

Emma (Female, 14–15) Lead

Curious and isolated. Emotionally intuitive and observant. Becomes the focus of the Entity’s attention.

The Entity (Female) Supporting

A physical, unsettling presence of pale flesh and darkness. Strong physical performance required. Heavy makeup FX and sclera lenses involved.

David (Male, late 30s to 40s) Supporting

Emma’s father. Practical and protective, pushed into a terrifying supernatural confrontation.

Father Benedict (Male, 60s) Supporting

A frail but determined priest attempting an exorcism. Spiritually authoritative despite physical weakness.

Submission Requirements:

Please click on the Google forms link below to submit your answers: https://forms.gle/sbUWJAjRM8iJmJFMA

items.text:
TONIGHT at The Two Brewers (Clapham) I’m beyond proud to welcome Martin Sherman on stage for The Show People Podcast LIVE.

Martin is one of the most important voices in queer theatre. His landmark play BENT opened at the Royal Court, transferred to the West End starring Ian McKellen, went on to Broadway (Richard Gere), and was later adapted for film. It’s a piece of writing that helped shape how queer lives are seen on stage.

His work spans decades across theatre and film, including ROSE (National Theatre/Broadway) and the BAFTA-nominated screenplay MRS HENDERSON PRESENTS, plus a body of writing that’s been produced in more than 60 countries.

Across theatre and film, Martin has been nominated for two Tony Awards, two Olivier Awards and two BAFTA Awards, and this evening is a chance to hear directly from a writer whose work has shaped queer storytelling for generations.

🎟️ Tickets are strictly limited to 100
💛 All profits support Queer Theatre’s work nurturing LGBTQIA+ talent and telling our stories

items.text:
Actors, be honest for a second. 

Have you ever looked at your headshot and thought:

“This doesn’t feel like me.”

Not bad.

Not unattractive, perhaps very much attractive but does not feel like YOU.

Just…someone else.

A shinier version.

A more “model-y” version.

A version casting will never meet in real life.

And that actually hurts your chances.

Because when your headshot does not look like you, casting feels the disconnect immediately.

They call you in expecting that energy… and a different one walks through the door. 

The gap breaks trust. 

Most headshot sessions create this problem because there’s:

No preparation

No real conversation 

No clarity around what you want to convey to casting

Just “stand there, soft eyes, chin down” and hope for the best.

Hope is not a strategy.

Before I photograph any actor, we talk first and weeks in advance NOT on the day of the shoot!!!

Not to sell you a shoot, but to figure out whether you even need an update or not. 

Sometimes your headshot is working for you, sometimes against you!

Sometimes the issue isn’t the photo, it’s the story your headshot is failing to tell.

If you do need an update, we prepare properly so there’s

X No guesswork

X No over-performing

X No leaving the session hoping there’s one unusable shot

During the shoot, I direct you the entire time, subtle shifts, real presence, grounded energy so the final image feels honest, believable, and castable.

If your headshot feels like a stranger who borrowed your face… that’s your sign.

Comment or DM me: Let’s talk headshots and I’ll DM you so we can chat!

Let’s talk and see if you actually need an update or not.

I’m currently based in Charlotte NC and looking for speaking role acting work, background acting work, soundtrack work or costume design work on film, TV shows or independent features as well.

After the huge success and high demand for our Phase I acting workshop, we’re excited to move forward with Phase II and open a brand-new beginners group.

ACTING Workshop

4-Week Practical Course

A hands-on acting course focused on confidence, presence, and truthful performance
in a playful, supportive, international environment.
No experience needed. Just curiosity.

What you’ll work on:

Week 1 Presence & Play
Confidence, focus, and imagination through simple acting games.
📅 Thursday, March 5th

Week 2 Truth in Dialogue
Listening, reacting, and speaking naturally on stage.
📅 Thursday, March 12th

Week 3 Character & Intention
Objectives, actions, and building believable characters.
📅 Thursday, March 19th

Week 4 Camera & Performance
Working on camera, short scenes, and performance awareness.
📅 Thursday, March 26th

Starting March 5th, every Thursday 

Why join?
• Build confidence and presence
• Learn practical acting tools
• Beginner-friendly and creative
• Safe space to try, fail, and grow
• Fun, social, and engaging

Perfect for
Actors • Performers • Public speakers • Improvers • Anyone wanting more confidence expressing themselves

📍 Warsaw City Center
🕡 19:00
🗣️ Language: English

Limited spots available

Instructor

Jordan Keates is a British actor trained at the Royal Central School of Speech and Drama in London.
He has worked across film, television, theatre, and commercials in the UK and Europe, including Netflix productions, Shakespeare tours, and international film projects.
Jordan brings a practical, grounded approach focused on truthful acting, clarity, and confidence on stage and on camera.

Choose what works for you: buy the full course or just a single session on the link below:

https://fienta.com/pl/camera-action-acting-workshop

Stay connected with Impact Warsaw
Instagram: @impactwarsaw &  @miguelatcomedy 
More events & updates: impactwarsaw.com/events
Discounts, inner-circle updates & secret extras
Join our Telegram community: https://t.me/+xJpuxiG5Au8xMmZk
Questions, collabs, or curious about taking part?
DM us, real people, real replies, real laughs.
We can’t wait to see you there. Come curious, leave inspired. 

PHASE I (beginners group)👇

https://fienta.com/pl/camera-action-acting-workshop-phase

Phase II – Advanced Group (for actors with experience only)
This group is designed for performers who already have acting experience.
The work is more demanding, faster paced, and focused on deeper scene work and performance precision.

👉 Apply & book Phase II here:
https://fienta.com/pl/camera-action-acting-workshop-168613

ETHNIC EXTRAS WANTED

WARSAW / WROCLAW

February 18th and 20th - availability on both days required

450 PLN per day 💵

I am looking for MEN extras to play the role of PRISONERS in Colombian prison of various ethnicities: Latinos and Black people

* dark hair, darker or black complexion, with or without facial hair, tattoes, aged 18+

Shooting days in Wroclaw - we will reimburse your travel expenses and provide accommodation!

items.text:
📣🎬 CASTING CALL – SHORT MOCKUMENTARY FILM

We are casting supporting speaking roles for RAPID, a 10-minute mockumentary graduation film produced as part of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

The film will be shot in Bristol from 2nd–6th March 2026.

This is a student project, unpaid with travel expenses and food provided, intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

STORY:
RAPID follows a small documentary crew as they capture former sprint star Ian Hitchworth’s attempted comeback through a chaotic athletics trial. Told in a dry, observational mockumentary style, the film blends awkward comedy with uncomfortable realism, allowing humour to emerge through timing, presence, and silence.

ROLES:

SAM – Changing Room Athlete
Male, 20s
Sarcastic and cynical. Quietly undermines Ian with dry interrogation and subtle looks to camera.

JOSH – Changing Room Athlete
Male, 20s
Sam’s double act partner. Dry, observant, and enjoys letting awkward pauses land. Aware of the camera.

DUNCAN – Changing Room Athlete
Male, 20s
Slow-witted but fascinated by the camera. Blank stares and odd sincerity. Competing more out of boredom than ambition.

These roles rely heavily on timing, subtle reactions, and grounded performances.

KEY INFO:
Location: Bristol
Shoot dates: 2nd–6th March 2026
Most roles required for one day only (TBC)
Payment: Voluntary (travel expenses & food provided)

TO APPLY:
Please send a headshot and CV (or Spotlight / Mandy link) to:
📩 rapidfilm2026@gmail.com

items.text:
CASTING CALL - ASAP

13/02/25

The Party No One Wanted (Short Film)

**A dark comedy about grief and family relationships.**

Robbie and Mary have to get through an excruciating memorial that has a DJ, karaoke and a pregnancy announcement / gender reveal planned by their half sister Lisa.

Please fill in this form if interested: [https://forms.gle/4N4tdaMwFQ6aBnga7](https://forms.gle/4N4tdaMwFQ6aBnga7) 

* **Shooting 6th - 9th March in TW19**
* Auditions in Elephant and Castle within the next few weeks
* **Travel Expenses Paid**
* There are also multiple smaller roles and extras needed please see the form for more information
* Student film hoping to go to Film festivals
* **Steve** (57-70yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Mary, Robbie and Lisa’s dad doesn’t get involved in the arguing he’s still devastated by the loss of his wife but insists he’s fine.
* **Lisa** (39-47yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Self centred and definitely doesn’t know whats appropriate at a memorial. 
* **Natalie** (49-65yrs)
   * A close family friend who has taken on a bit of a motherly role to everyone, kind and soft spoken.
* **Bill** (50-65yrs) 
   * The drunk best friend of steve who has awful timing for his awkward comments. Very funny character

**Character Bios: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing)** **

**Director’s Statement: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing)

🎭 PERFORMING OPPORTUNITY – CASTING FOR 2026 🎭

✨ MPP Character Entertainment is now casting performers for 2026! ✨

We have an exciting year ahead filled with magical parties, immersive events and fairytale experiences! We are looking for talented performers to join our growing team!

📍 Location: Manchester & North West, UK

⸻

🌟 About the Role:
• Most events are based in Manchester and across the North West, so local performers are strongly preferred
• 🚗 A full driving licence and access to a car is required (petrol costs covered)
• 👑 Casting for a range of characters, you may be suited to multiple roles
• 🎭 A background in musical theatre, acting or performance is ideal
• 💖 We’re looking for performers who are bubbly, kind, reliable and confident working with children

We offer flexible opportunities including temporary work, short-term contracts, weekly bookings, and cover shifts, perfect whether you want regular work or occasional gigs ✨
⸻

📩 How to Apply:
Please send your CV and a recent headshot to:
📧Manager@MPPCharacterEntertainment.com
Or drop us a private message to register your interest 💌

🌐 Website: www.manchesterprincessparties.co.uk

We can’t wait to welcome new performers and create even more magical moments in 2026! ✨
MPP Character Entertainment

🌹 WALENTYNKI ZA NAMI, ALE MUZYKA TRWA! 🎶💖

Mamy nadzieję, że Wasz weekend był pełen miłości! ❤️ Jeśli wczoraj śpiewaliście dla kogoś bliskiego, to mamy dla Was ważną wiadomość: teraz czas, aby usłyszało Was nasze jury! 🎙️✨

Odliczanie nabiera tempa! Do końca przyjmowania zgłoszeń w konkursie „Dźwięki Miłości 2026” zostało już tylko:

🗓️ 14 DNI! (DOKŁADNIE 2 TYGODNIE) ⏳🔥

To ostatnia prosta, by stać się częścią tego wyjątkowego wydarzenia on-line. Pamiętajcie, że w naszym konkursie nie liczy się tylko technika, ale przede wszystkim emocje i prawda, którą przekazujecie w swojej piosence. 🥰🎹

Nie czekajcie na ostatnią chwilę, serwery lubią płatać figle, a my chcemy mieć pewność, że Wasz głos do nas dotrze! 💨🎬

Zróbcie sobie prezent po Walentynkach i dajcie szansę swoim marzeniom! 🏆🌈

🔗 Zapisz się tutaj: https://magiczne-melodie.pl/dzwieki-milosci-zapisz-sie/ 
📜 Regulamin: https://magiczne-melodie.pl/dzwieki-milosci-regulamin/

items.text:
Actor mark your calendars and improve your craft for February 14th—a day filled with creativity, collaboration, and cinematic magic! 

Join us for an incredible opportunity to learn, network, and bring your film aspirations to life alongside fellow passionate creatives. 

This free introductory filmmaking workshop in Los Angeles is your chance to connect with filmmakers who are just as excited about storytelling as you are. Dive into the world of filmmaking, where you'll not only share ideas and inspire one another but also roll up your sleeves and create unforgettable movies together. At Empowering Filmmakers, we believe that everyone has a story to tell. We provide everything you need to make your vision a reality—state-of-the-art cameras, lighting, props, costumes, and even locations. You’ll be amazed at what you can achieve when you work together! Help each other bring your ideas to life as you take turns behind and in front of the camera. This is not just a workshop; it’s a chance to join a vibrant community of aspiring filmmakers who will cheer you on as you embark on your creative journey.

Complete the form to reserve your seat, and get ready to turn your cinematic dreams into reality. We can’t wait to create with you! https://forms.gle/LVapuLwm12zmv7Xz5

Vertical Microdramas are rapidly reshaping how stories are told, cast, and consumed and the industry leaders driving that change are coming together for one essential conversation.

We’re excited to invite you to attend the Vertical Microdrama Panel, presented by theWorkbook and Center Stage. This live, virtual event brings together top casting professionals, agents, producers, directors, and actors who are actively working in the vertical space.

You’ll hear firsthand insights on:

How vertical microdramas are being cast and produced

What creators and casting teams are looking for right now

Where opportunities are emerging for actors and filmmakers

How this format is influencing the future of short-form storytelling

items.text:
Landmark gay playwright and author of Bent, Martin Sherman will be joining me on stage at The Two Brewers this Wednesday, as we talk through his extraordinary life and career, and what it’s meant to tell queer stories across the decades.

Born in Philadelphia and educated at Boston University, Martin now lives in London, and his writing has been produced in more than sixty countries. He is renowned for his Tony-nominated landmark play Bent, which opened at the Royal Court and transferred to the West End starring Ian McKellen, before going on to Broadway starring Richard Gere. The play was later revived at the National Theatre and adapted for the screen in 1998 starring Clive Owen. Bent went on to win the Dramatists Guild’s Hull-Warriner Award, and remains one of the most vital pieces of queer theatre ever written.

His theatre work spans decades and includes Rose (National Theatre and Broadway), Gently Down the Stream (Public Theater and Park Theatre), Onassis (Novello Theatre), Some Sunny Day (Hampstead), A Madhouse in Goa (Lyric Hammersmith and Apollo), When She Danced (King’s Head and Gielgud), Messiah (Hampstead and Aldwych), plus Absolutely! (Perhaps), his acclaimed reworking of Pirandello’s Right You Are (If You Think So) at Wyndham’s Theatre. He also wrote the Broadway musical The Boy from Oz and created a major stage adaptation of E. M. Forster’s A Passage to India (Riverside Theatre and BAM). New work continues, with I’ll Be Seeing You premiering at Pitlochry Festival Theatre in September 2026.

On screen, Martin’s credits include Mrs Henderson Presents (BAFTA-nominated), The Roman Spring of Mrs. Stone, Callas Forever, Alive and Kicking, and The Clothes in the Wardrobe (released in the US as The Summer House). He is currently writing Frank and Percy for the screen, with a major cast including Sir Ian McKellen and Roger Allam.

Across theatre and film, Martin has been nominated for two Tony Awards, two Olivier Awards and two BAFTA Awards, and this evening is a chance to hear directly from a writer whose work has shaped queer storytelling for generations.

🎟️ Tickets are strictly limited to 100, with all profits supporting Queer Theatre’s work nurturing queer talent and telling LGBTQIA+ stories.

Further details for each role can be found in the individual listings/images below, or on backstage (link at the bottom of this post)

LEAD

SUPPORTING

items.text:
Hey guys,

I’m sure it’s not just me who’s asked the age-old actor question… where the hell do I find a **good** scene or monologue?

After wasting way too much time digging around the internet, I built the answer: [www.auditionscenes.com](http://www.auditionscenes.com/)

It’s a curated monologue and acting scene archive and finder. Hundreds of scenes are being added weekly.

**What it does:**

• Curated monologues and scenes from film, TV and theatre
• Clean, ready-to-download PDFs
• Proper filters: accent (Irish, American, etc.), age range, genre, classical vs contemporary, character type and more
• Monologue Match tool that suggests material based on your details
• Optional Director’s Notes for every scene, breaking down beats, context and character psychology
• Save favourites and build your own shortlist

You can browse freely. Downloading and rating are part of the paid membership.

For launch, if you want unlimited yearly access, you can use code **fnqixeA0** for 15% off.

This has been years in the making, and I'm seriously excited to finally get it out there.

We are producing a short interview series featuring models, actors, beauty professionals etc to find out their secrets and daily regimen on looking young and feeling great. Old young we are looking for real people, giving real advice.

It's a relaxed 15 minute video interview (via Streamyard) and no prep is necessary. Just a fun interview with you sharing your advice :)

If interested, please send us a pic and we will contact you in the next few days.

- Format : 15 min interview
- Location/Platform : Remote / Streamyard or Zoom
- You will receive footage
- $20.00 for 15 min of fun conversation and sharing your advice.

Thanks and looking forward to hearing from you soon.

Improtheater-Urlaub am Meer in Süd-Spanien     

"Kopf aus - Flow an"

☆ 8 Tage Improtheater über Ostern, in der paradiesichen Oase mit Pool, Hängematten, Sauna, schönen Appartments mit Terrasse und unserem Restaurant mit Panoramablick aufs Meer.

☆ Jeden Tag gibt es 4 Stunden Improworkshops mit einer vielseitigen Mischung aus Improspielen, Schauspiel- und Rollenarbeit, Storytelling, und Szenen voller Genres, Status und Emotionen.

☆ Alles inklusive: Improtheater-Workshops, Bio-Vollpension (inklusive aller Getränke!), komfortables Appartment, ein Sauna-Abend und Flughafentransfer insgesamt nur 1.383 € !♡

🌴☀️ **DANCERS & SINGERS WANTED – GREECE 2026!** ☀️🌴
**MALE DANCERS & MALE SINGERS ESPECIALLY WANTED**
(Female performers are very welcome too!)
📌 **Applicants must have an EU passport**

📍 5★ Resorts in Greece
📅 Summer Season 2026
🗓 Start: **Dancers: flexible from March up to August 1st 2026** | **Singers: April/May 2026**

Ready for an unforgettable summer under the Greek sun? 🇬🇷✨
Join our international Entertainment Teams and perform in professional **Production Shows** in stunning 5-star resorts.

🎬 Watch our show productions:
[https://youtu.be/9PdbLO--GX4?si=W8fKURLEWPjE9bCG](https://youtu.be/9PdbLO--GX4?si=W8fKURLEWPjE9bCG)

## 🎭 WHO WE ARE LOOKING FOR:

✅ Strong, versatile **male dancers** (especially needed)
✅ Charismatic **male singers** (especially needed)
✅ Female dancers and singers are also very welcome
✅ Confident, energetic stage performers
✅ Team players with good English (other languages are a plus)
✅ Artists ready for an international experience
✅ **EU passport holders only**

## 🎤 YOUR ROLE:

✨ Perform in high-quality evening Production Shows
✨ Take part in rehearsals and show preparations
✨ Engage with guests and represent the entertainment team professionally
✨ Bring energy, charisma, and positive vibes on and off stage

## 💼 WHAT WE OFFER – A COMPLETE & CAREFREE PACKAGE:

✔️ 3–7 month contracts in luxury 5★ resorts
✔️ Competitive net monthly salary (based on experience and skills)
✔️ Full social security, pension & accident insurance
✔️ Free accommodation
✔️ Three meals per day & beverages in hotel restaurants
✔️ Flight reimbursement up to €300
✔️ Airport transfer to the resort
✔️ Daily and evening costumes provided
✔️ One day off per week
✔️ Free trainings and workshops
✔️ Bonuses depending on hotel facilities

🌟 **ONLINE AUDITIONS NOW OPEN!**

Make Summer 2026 your best season yet!

📩 Send your CV and showreel to:
**tamira@palmera-agency.com**

See you in Greece! 🇬🇷✨

Teatr Muzyczny Paris prowadzi nabór artystów sceny muzycznej do profesjonalnych produkcji musicalowych. 🤩

Poszukujemy aktorów, wokalistów i tancerzy o ugruntowanym warsztacie oraz wysokiej świadomości scenicznej, gotowych do pracy w wymagającym, autorskim środowisku artystycznym. ✨

Oferujemy:

☑️pracę w profesjonalnym zespole artystycznym,
☑️udział w ambitnych, autorskich produkcjach scenicznych,
☑️rozwój pod kierunkiem uznanych realizatorów i kreatorów sceny musicalowej,
☑️jasno określone, profesjonalne i stabilne warunki współpracy.

📍Premiera naszej pierwszej produkcji – dance musicalu „HIGH HEELS” – odbędzie się 28 maja 2026 r. Próby planowane są od kwietnia.

➡️Proces preselekcji oparty jest na analizie nadesłanych materiałów. Wybrane osoby zostaną zaproszone na casting, który odbędzie się 22–23 lutego. Prosimy o przesyłanie kompletnych zgłoszeń na adres: casting@teatrparis.pl

⚡ Eksperci wyłaniają 4 finalistów;

⚡ Finałowe kapele zagrają na żywo w Krakowie, a profesjonalne jury wybierze zwycięzcę Przeglądu Kapel Rockowych UEK 2026!

Do ostatniego odcinka 20 sezonu GLINIARZY szukam: 

1. Maria Kolba (48) – gosposia, niepozorna. Koniecznie szczupła i drobna. Miła aparycja. 
Data: 24 i 25.02
Stawka: 700 zł netto za całość

2. Iwona Siewczyk (29) – zadbana brunetka, chętnie zrobione usta i sztuczny biust. Żona Siewczyka, która go zdradza.
Obowiązkowe PRAWO JAZDY!
Data: 24 i 26.02
Stawka: 900 zł netto za całość

3. Hubert Kolba (24) – syn Marii, przeciętny chłopak, zwykła sylwetka.
Data: 25.02
Stawka: 250 zł netto

4. Ratownik 1  (25) – ratownik medyczny, przeciętny facet.
Data: 26.02
Stawka: 200 zł netto

Zainteresowane osoby proszę o zgłoszenia wyłącznie poprzez e-mail na adres: outsetola@op.pl

Proszę, by zgłaszały się tylko osoby, które jeszcze nie grały w tym sezonie (od września).

W tytule e-maila proszę o wpisanie nazwy postaci.

W treści:
- Wiek, wzrost, waga
- Numer telefonu
- Informacje o dotychczasowym doświadczeniu przed kamerą
- Linki do swoich materiałów video: wizytówka/demo/scenki ze swoim udziałem
- Aktualne zdjęcie

Nie zwracamy kosztów dojazdu i noclegu. Warszawa.

items.text:
📣🎬 CASTING CALL – SHORT MOCKUMENTARY FILM

We are casting supporting speaking roles for RAPID, a 10-minute mockumentary graduation film produced as part of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

The film will be shot in Bristol from 2nd–6th March 2026.

This is a student project, unpaid with travel expenses and food provided, intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

STORY:
RAPID follows a small documentary crew as they capture former sprint star Ian Hitchworth’s attempted comeback through a chaotic athletics trial. Told in a dry, observational mockumentary style, the film blends awkward comedy with uncomfortable realism, allowing humour to emerge through timing, presence, and silence.

ROLES:

SAM – Changing Room Athlete
Male, 20s
Sarcastic and cynical. Quietly undermines Ian with dry interrogation and subtle looks to camera.

JOSH – Changing Room Athlete
Male, 20s
Sam’s double act partner. Dry, observant, and enjoys letting awkward pauses land. Aware of the camera.

DUNCAN – Changing Room Athlete
Male, 20s
Slow-witted but fascinated by the camera. Blank stares and odd sincerity. Competing more out of boredom than ambition.

These roles rely heavily on timing, subtle reactions, and grounded performances.

KEY INFO:
Location: Bristol
Shoot dates: 2nd–6th March 2026
Most roles required for one day only (TBC)
Payment: Voluntary (travel expenses & food provided)

TO APPLY:
Please send a headshot and CV (or Spotlight / Mandy link) to:
📩 rapidfilm2026@gmail.com

🎉 EXTRAS NEEDED – PARTY SCENE (MANCHESTER) 🎉
We’re looking for extras to be part of a Halloween party scene in our student short film Worn 👀

📍 Location: Manchester

📅 Date: Wednesday 25th February

⏰ Time: From 13:30 (exact wrap time TBC)

We’re after people aged 18+ who are happy to bring good energy and help us create a lively, slightly chaotic party atmosphere. No acting experience needed – just enthusiasm!

This is a great chance to gain on-set experience, meet other creatives, and be part of an exciting independent project.

Interested? Fill out the Google Form linked in the comments/caption 🎭✨

Feel free to share with anyone who might be up for it!

sharedPost.text:
Please help us reach our target. 🙏💙

As each day passes and we move closer to the deadline, we’re urging everyone to visit our crowdfunder and get involved. We truly want to make this film the best it can be, and having the right equipment is the way forward. 🎬✨

Everyone involved is giving their time and energy for free, driven by passion and belief in this project. Our dream is to take this film to an international audience and put Runcorn, Halton, and the North West right at the front of independent cinema. 🌍🏆

All it takes is a few quid and a share. Every single bit of support makes a real difference.

Please help us make this film the best it can be.
Made in Runcorn. By Runcorn. 💙🎥

items.text:
**Free Self-Tape Coaching This Week for Qualified Actors **

**(New Actors Welcome) **

(Normally $65)

If you’ve sent in a pile of Self-Tapes last year and gotten nothing but silence back, that messes with your head. You start replaying your choices. You tweak wardrobe. You second guess the read. You wonder if casting directors even watched past the slate.

Most actors I talk to aren’t missing talent. They’re missing clarity.

They’re “acting” instead of being a real person in a real place having a real experience. And nobody ever slowed down long enough to show them the difference.

That’s where I come in.

This week, I’m opening up a limited number of **Free Zoom Coaching and Consultation sessions on your self tapes**.
Normally this is a $65 session.
This week, it’s free.

We’ll hop on Zoom, go over a script, and I’ll show you exactly what casting directors are responding to and what’s getting in the way. No fluff. No generic notes. Just clear, practical direction that actually shifts your work.

Work and prepare smarter in 2026 and get results. Feel and BE a real working actor this year.

Spots are limited and once they’re gone, they’re gone.

**DM me to grab a spot. Name, How long you’v been acting, and Where you’re based.**

***Serious actors only.**

***Must be 18 yrs old.**

items.text:
CASTING CALL

Project: indie film

Plot:

A woman in her 20s drifts through friendships, impulses, and quiet disappointments, unsure of who she is or how to move forward. As her world begins to fracture, she is forced to confront her own patterns of blame, desire, and avoidance. Through solitude and fleeting human connections, she slowly learns to sit with sadness, not as something to escape, but as a guide toward self-understanding and the courage to begin again.

 

Shooting dates: Mid-End of March 2026 (mostly weekends)

Shooting location: Vancouver and the greater area

 

Please submit your resume, headshot(s), and demo reel or self-tape by email: [theprivilegeofsorrow@gmail.com](mailto:theprivilegeofsorrow@gmail.com)

 

Volunteer Position

 

PARTY FRIEND #1

Male, 20s

Cocky, confrontational party goer. Loves night thrills; beach partying, running, shouting, high energy after a wild house party.

 

PARTY FRIEND #2

Male/female/non-binary, 20s

Easygoing follower, impulsive and playful. Down for anything; night beach run, laughing, hyping the group, physical, carefree energy.

 

PARTY FRIEND #3

Male/female/non-binary, 20s

At a chaotic party, they notice a girl passed out. Later, in a quieter moment, they end up talking while the party continues.

 

GLASSES

Male, 20s
Tall, robust, dominant presence. Confident, physical, impulsive; intense hookup energy in a crowded party setting.

 

GYM EMPLOYEE

Neutral, mildly defensive, trained to de-escalate. Repeats policy language automatically, avoids eye contact, prioritizes rules over empathy.

 

GAS STATION WORKER

Irritable, territorial, quick to escalate. Defensive authority figure; confrontational energy in a late-night, mundane conflict over a vending machine.

 

We are also casting background performers for the party scenes. Please indicate your interest when submitting.

Project: indie film

Plot:

A woman in her 20s drifts through friendships, impulses, and quiet disappointments, unsure of who she is or how to move forward. As her world begins to fracture, she is forced to confront her own patterns of blame, desire, and avoidance. Through solitude and fleeting human connections, she slowly learns to sit with sadness, not as something to escape, but as a guide toward self-understanding and the courage to begin again.

 

Shooting dates: Mid-End of March 2026 (mostly weekends)

CASTING CALL - ASAP

13/02/25

The Party No One Wanted (Short Film)

**A dark comedy about grief and family relationships.**

Robbie and Mary have to get through an excruciating memorial that has a DJ, karaoke and a pregnancy announcement / gender reveal planned by their half sister Lisa.

Please fill in this form if interested: [https://forms.gle/4N4tdaMwFQ6aBnga7](https://forms.gle/4N4tdaMwFQ6aBnga7) 

* **Shooting 6th - 9th March in TW19**
* Auditions in Elephant and Castle within the next few weeks
* **Travel Expenses Paid**
* There are also multiple smaller roles and extras needed please see the form for more information
* Student film hoping to go to Film festivals
* **Steve** (57-70yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Mary, Robbie and Lisa’s dad doesn’t get involved in the arguing he’s still devastated by the loss of his wife but insists he’s fine.
* **Lisa** (39-47yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Self centred and definitely doesn’t know whats appropriate at a memorial. 
* **Natalie** (49-65yrs)
   * A close family friend who has taken on a bit of a motherly role to everyone, kind and soft spoken.
* **Bill** (50-65yrs) 
   * The drunk best friend of steve who has awful timing for his awkward comments. Very funny character

**Character Bios: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing)** **

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with only cheating. Based on a real story.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

⚡️Need to create your first showreel / freshen up your old one?⚡️
Happy Sunday all!

I provide a very affordable showreel service for new or established actors/directors/cinematographers/comedians/hobbyists etc.

Basically, send me your footage (or I can try and source it for you online if it's commercially aired) and I shall edit it together into a lovely reel.

Please see samples of recent clients in the link below 😎

I'm an actor myself so I know how frustrating it can be, especially when you're starting out, to collate your footage together to get more work, without wanting to spend a fortune.

My rates are £20/hour, with duration of work depending on how much footage you have. The average reels have been around £80-£100 for my clients. Much more affordable than the companies that charge £250+ !!

For any further info / enquiries / to book my services, drop me an email and I'll respond as quickly as I can:

reelsforanyone@gmail.com

I'll look forward to hearing from you.

Thanks!

😎

www.youtube.com/@Reels.For.Anyone

# CASTING CALL – PAID COMMERCIAL SHOOT – BIRMINGHAM

As part of a commercial that will be broadcast in Argentina, we are looking for actors and actresses to portray the following roles:

**•⁠  ⁠1 female model, aged 25–40, Argentinian / Latin type**

**•⁠  ⁠1 male model, aged 30–35, athletic profile, Latin type**

**•⁠  ⁠1 male actor, aged 40–45, Latin type**

**•⁠  ⁠Extras: men and women of all ages, Argentinian / Latin type**

## Practical Information:

Shooting date: **February 24, 2026**

Location: **Birmingham, UK**

**Paid shoot**

## How to Apply:

Before applying, please register on **simplekast.com **so we can process your application.

Interested candidates can send their pictures, showreels and presentation video to this email address : 

**angelinebacar.simplekast@gmail.com**

We look forward to bringing this project to life with you!

*SIMPLE KAST TEAM*

items.text:
**🎬 CASTING – ROLA KOBIECA (EPIZOD)**

**Krótkometrażowy film fabularny „JUTRO BĘDZIE LEPIEJ”**
Projekt artystyczny / festiwalowy

Szukamy aktorki do **krótkiej, symbolicznej sceny intymnej** w filmie fabularnym osadzonym w Warszawie lat 90.

**🎭 ROLA**

**KOBIETA (19–23 lata)**
Epizod – scena bez dialogu.

Scena ma charakter **intymny, ale w pełni artystyczny** – oparta na nastroju, światłocieniu i sugestii.
**Nie będzie pokazywana twarz ani rozpoznawalny wizerunek.**
Widoczne będą wyłącznie zarysy sylwetek, detale ciała, ruch, światło i cień.

Nie jest to scena erotyczna w sensie dosłownym – **nie ma dosłowności, nie ma ekspozycji**, całość podporządkowana jest dramaturgii filmu.

**📌 Informacje organizacyjne**
* scena bardzo krótka (kilkanaście sekund w montażu),
* realizowana z pełnym poszanowaniem komfortu aktorki,
* zamknięty plan, minimalna ekipa,
* możliwość wcześniejszego omówienia i ustalenia granic,

**👤 Kryteria**
* wiek: **19–23 lata**
* zgrabna, proporcjonalna sylwetka
* naturalność, swoboda ruchu
* doświadczenie aktorskie **nie jest wymagane**, ale mile widziane

**📌 Warunki udziału**

Projekt realizowany w formule artystycznej / festiwalowej.
Udział **nieodpłatny (świadczenie artystyczne)**.

Zapewniamy:
✔ profesjonalną realizację
✔ pełną dyskrecję
✔ catering / zwrot kosztów
✔ materiały do portfolio (na życzenie)

Zgłoszenia wyłącznie w wiadomości prywatnej. Proszę nie zgłaszać się w komentarzach.
W zgłoszeniu: wiek, wzrost, przynajmniej jedno zdjęci pokazujące sylwetkę, np. obcisły strój lub kostium kąpielowy.

ETHNIC EXTRAS WANTED

WARSAW / WROCLAW

February 18th and 20th - availability on both days required

450 PLN per day 💵

I am looking for MEN extras to play the role of PRISONERS in Colombian prison of various ethnicities: Latinos and Black people

* dark hair, darker or black complexion, with or without facial hair, tattoes, aged 18+

Shooting days in Wroclaw - we will reimburse your travel expenses and provide accommodation!

Please send your applications to: patrycja@podtytulem.pl

In the subject line: PRISON

In the body of the email: your first and last name, age, phone number, city, and a PHOTO OF YOUR FACE AND FIGURE taken on the day of application only

🎬 CASTING CALL – PAID PRINCIPAL ROLES 

(ATLANTA LOCAL HIRE)

CORRUPTION OFFICER – Non-Union Pilot Episode

📍 Atlanta, GA

📅 February 18, 2026 (One-Day Shoot | 4–5 Hours)

💵 Paid Principal Day Rate | Non-Union | Independent Production

Production is casting two (2) East Asian male actors for a gritty, character-driven pilot set inside a correctional facility. 

These are performance-forward roles requiring strong physical presence, emotional control, and compelling nonverbal acting.

**CHEN (22–32)**

Male, East Asian, lean build

Older brother

Controlled, observant, strategic

Minimal dialogue

Must convey internal power and authority through stillness

Portrays an incarcerated individual

**JIN (20–30)**

Male, East Asian, lean/athletic build

Younger brother

Intense yet disciplined

Strong physical performer

Comfortable with choreographed fight sequences

Portrays an incarcerated individual

Both Roles:
* Physical performance with choreographed fight sequences (no high-risk stunts)
* Martial arts or movement training a plus
* Mandarin or Cantonese ability a plus (brief dialogue)
* Must be comfortable portraying incarcerated characters
* Atlanta local hire only

This project emphasizes physical storytelling and screen presence. 

We are seeking actors who can command attention with minimal dialogue and controlled intensity.

📩 TO SUBMIT:

Email:** info.coshort@gmail.com**

Subject Line: ROLE: CHEN or ROLE: JIN

* Headshot

(ATLANTA LOCAL HIRE)

CORRUPTION OFFICER – Non-Union Pilot Episode

📍 Atlanta, GA

📅 February 18, 2026 (One-Day Shoot | 4–5 Hours)

💵 Paid Principal Day Rate | Non-Union | Independent Production

Production is casting two (2) East Asian male actors for a gritty, character-driven pilot set inside a correctional facility. 

These are performance-forward roles requiring strong physical presence, emotional control, and compelling nonverbal acting.

**CHEN (22–32)**

Male, East Asian, lean build

Older brother

Controlled, observant, strategic

Minimal dialogue

Must convey internal power and authority through stillness

Portrays an incarcerated individual

**JIN (20–30)**

Male, East Asian, lean/athletic build

Younger brother

Intense yet disciplined

Strong physical performer

Comfortable with choreographed fight sequences

Portrays an incarcerated individual

Both Roles:
* Physical performance with choreographed fight sequences (no high-risk stunts)
* Martial arts or movement training a plus
* Mandarin or Cantonese ability a plus (brief dialogue)
* Must be comfortable portraying incarcerated characters
* Atlanta local hire only

This project emphasizes physical storytelling and screen presence. 

We are seeking actors who can command attention with minimal dialogue and controlled intensity.

📩 TO SUBMIT:

Email:** info.coshort@gmail.com**

Subject Line: ROLE: CHEN or ROLE: JIN

Please include:
* Headshot

‼️👁️CASTING CALL👁️‼️

Final Run Company are casting for one of their upcoming Camden Fringe shows, The Silence After, an anthology play focussing on three stories in the aftermath of a supernatural event.

To audition, send us either an Acting Showreel OR Spotlight along with a monologue from a horror or sci-fi movie/play to finalruncompany@gmail.com with the heading ‘TSA Audition’

If successful, you will be asked to be called back for a recall, before the final casting decision is made.

Any questions or queries message us on Instagram or email us at finalruncompany@gmail.com

GOOD LUCK!!!

*TW: Violence, implied sexual assault, drug usage, references to abuse, references to haebophilia, suicide.

*NOTE: This is not the final list of trigger warnings as the play is still in development, those in the recall process will be told in depth about the current draft and the procedures in place to safely go about these topics.

items.text:
Paid opportunity to perform at Edinburgh Fringe- last chance to apply
OPEN AUDITIONS – BLOOMIN’ CHURCH!

Edinburgh Festival Fringe 2026 + South West Tour

PAID – Equity Rates

DROPS – Making waves through the arts is casting performers aged 18+ for Bloomin’ Church!, a heartfelt new play heading to the Edinburgh Festival Fringe in summer 2026, followed by a South West tour in October 2026.

HOW TO AUDITION

Auditions will take place across a three-stage process:

Stage 1 – Self-Tape Submission

Submit a self-tape audition.

Deadline: Sunday 15th February at 6:00pm

Stage 2 – Individual Callbacks

Sherwell United Church (Chapel), Plymouth, PL4 8ER

Friday 27th February

Stage 3 – Final Callback (Group Workshop)

Sherwell United Church (Chapel), Plymouth

Saturday 28th February

AUDITION PACK

Full character breakdowns, role requirements, and self-tape instructions can be found here:

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1sbwIgm9kKo5wbnTLrEYqXTmuOFDyGCXm/view?usp=share_link

Strong acting required, with some singing and movement.

Professional and amateur performers welcome.

Inclusive casting

DROPS welcomes performers of all backgrounds, identities, and experiences.

DROPS - making waves through the arts

# **Casting Call**

University of Westminster Graduation Film: See You At The Funktion is looking for 5 roles!

Logline: A young Hungarian-English woman who struggles to reveal that she’s moving abroad at her grandma’s disco-themed 70th birthday party

**ROLES ARE UNPAID, MEALS, & TRAVEL COVERED. Shooting FEB 21-24 in NW London - rehearsal this WEDS need availability ALL OF THESE DAYS**

Aunt Jess, Aged 30-55, Supporting

Uncle Jeff, Aged 30-55, Supporting

Elderly Women X2, Aged 50+, Supporting

Stephan (DAD), Aged 30-55, Supporting

**Email me at caitlyn.madeley101@gmail.com if interested - THE SOONER THE BETTER.**

Kultur am Brahmsee präsentiert den 4. Langwedeler KurzFilmAbend am Samstag, den 7. März 2026 um 19:00 Uhr

Wieder einmal laden Rudi Schmedemann und der Langwedeler Filmemacher und Medianpädagoge Johann Schultz zum gemeinsamen Filmegucken ein! Filmemacher aus Schleswig-Holstein und Hamburg zeigen ihre Werke, die oft im Rahmen des „Nur 48-Stunden-Wettbewerbs“ entstanden sind. Außerdem wird es auch wieder einen Block Musikvideos geben.

Die Resonanz auf diese inzwischen zum 4. Mal stattfindende Veranstaltung zeigt, was für tolle Filme nicht nur in Hollywood, sondern auch in unserer direkten Nachbarschaft entstehen. Natürlich stehen die Filmemacher auch für Gespräche und Fachsimpeleien zur Verfügung! Unser Sportheim-Team Baker und Eva sorgen wie immer für euer leibliches Wohl!

Eintritt 5.- Euro, Anmeldung erforderlich bis zum 6. März.

Anmeldung unter kultur-am-brahmsee@langwedel-sh.de oder telefonisch unter 0175-4150564 (bitte erst ab 17 Uhr anrufen). Bitte nicht über Facebook anmelden!

Adresse:

 

Gaststätte Sportheim Langwedel

Am Sportplatz 1b

24631 Langwedel 

Beste Grüße, euer Rudi!

items.text:
🔥 TWO POWERFUL DANCE SOLOS AT KNAP! 🔥
📅 December 10, 2025 at 7 PM
📍 KNAP – Concert Hall, Ivanićgradska 41a, Zagreb
✨ FREE ENTRY!

Join us for a captivating evening within KNAP’s Offbeat program, featuring two striking solo performances that delve deep into the questions of identity, transformation, and the inevitability of change.

In I SAMO, choreographer and performer Bruno Isaković confronts the modern obsession with constant self-improvement. Through an intimate, physical dialogue, the piece dismantles the myth of the “better version of oneself” and opens a space for sincerity, vulnerability, and authentic presence.

In KRAJ KRAJEVA, performed by Mia Zalukar, the focus shifts toward the countless endings—subtle, unexpected, or monumental—that punctuate our daily lives. The work invites us to reflect on how we face closure, what we resist or accept, and how endings might quietly reframe our beginnings.

Together, these two solos offer a powerful meditation on who we are while striving, changing, finishing, and beginning again. Expect an evening of deeply felt movement, thought-provoking concepts, and artists who approach the stage with uncompromising honesty.

🎟️ Free tickets available at the link in the first comment.
Don’t miss this unique double bill!

sharedPost.text:
🎭 KNAPOV OFFBEAT: I SAMO / KRAJ KRAJEVA
📅 Srijeda, 10. 12. 2025. u 19:00
📍 Koncertna dvorana KNAP
🎟️ Ulaz slobodan
Ivanićgradska 41 a

Dvije snažne solo izvedbe, dva različita pogleda na naše svakodnevne napore, očekivanja, početke i završetke. Večer koja propituje tko smo dok se pokušavamo (pre)oblikovati — i što nam sve na tom putu ostaje na rubovima.

⸻

I SAMO

👤 Autor i izvedba: Bruno Isaković
🎼 Glazba: Hrvoje Nikšić
🎙️ Glas: Alan Watts (Out of Your Mind – lectures)
🎬 Produkcija: UO Malo sutra
🎭 Koprodukcija: Domino

U svijetu u kojem se od nas traži da budemo „bolje verzije sebe“, Bruno Isaković u svom solo komadu razotkriva paradoks osobnog rasta: što ako je želja za neprekidnim usavršavanjem samo zamka — i ako zapravo najviše rastemo kad dopustimo sebi da ne budemo savršeni?
„I samo“ je koreografski poziv na iskrenost, ranjivost i autentičnost, na tijelo koje ne glumi hologram nego govori istinu.

⸻

KRAJ KRAJEVA

👤 Koreografija i izvedba: Mia Zalukar
🎼 Glazba: Hrvoje Nikšić
📝 Dramaturgija: Margareta Sinković
🎨 Umjetnička suradnica: Lucija Barišić
🎬 Produkcija: UO Malo sutra
🎭 Koprodukcija: Domino

Koliko „krajeva“ možemo doživjeti u jednom jedinom danu? I možemo li ih prepoznati, označiti, ispratiti?
U solo izvedbi „Kraj krajeva“, Mia Zalukar otvara prostor za razgovor s neizbježnim završecima — onim krupnim i onim sitnim, svakodnevnim. Kroz cikličnu izvedbu, pokret i promišljanje, ona stvara intiman dijalog s prolaznošću i propituje kako se pripremamo za kraj… i što se dogodi kad ga napokon prihvatimo.

⸻

🎟️ Ulaz slobodan — pridružite nam se na večeri koja otvara prostor za promjenu, prihvaćanje i novo gledanje na sebe i svijet. 

Besplatne ulaznice mozete preuzti preko linka u prvom komentaru.

🎬 CASTING DO FILMU Fabularnego
🎭 ROLA: ADAM  – GŁÓWNA ROLA MĘSKA

Wiek aktora: 16–20 lat (mile widziany młody debiutant)

Wygląd: atrakcyjny, charyzmatyczny, ciekawa uroda – „twarz, którą się zapamiętuje”

Kogo szukamy?

Chłopaka inteligentnego, bystrego, z naturalnym luzem i wewnętrzną siłą. Adam to lider z przypadku – nie krzyczy, nie popisuje się, ale ludzie za nim idą. Ma w sobie coś zawadiackiego, szelmowskiego, ale też wrażliwość i empatię.

 

🎭 ROLA: WANDA – GŁÓWNA ROLA ŻEŃSKA

Wiek aktorki: 16–20 lat

Wygląd: bardzo ładna, naturalna uroda, wdzięk, wyraziste oczy

👉 Szukamy nowej Poli Raksy – świeżości, magnetyzmu, klasy.

Kogo szukamy?

Dziewczyny inteligentnej, odważnej, z charakterem. Wanda nie jest „dziewczyną w tle” – to partnerka Adama, często emocjonalnie odważniejsza od chłopaków. Potrafi postawić na swoim, ale nie traci ciepła.

📩 INFORMACJE CASTINGOWE

Projekt kinowy, duża produkcja przygodowa

Zdjęcia: 2026

Casting otwarty również na utalentowanych debiutantów

Prosimy o: zdjęcia (portret + sylwetka), krótkie bio, wiek, wizytówka jako link do YouTube, kontakt

 

Prosimy o przysyłanie zgłoszeń na adres: sky.zgloszenia@gmail.com

items.text:
UCCS DIGITAL FILMMAKING CAPSTONE FILM AUDITIONS

Our UCCS capstone film production students are gearing up to shoot their capstone short films, and this year there will be a whopping 18 films to audition for! Auditions begin this Saturday, February 14 and continue through March 1. I try to structure the auditions and the film shoots in a way that is as actor-friendly as possible:
* Auditions are held on UCCS campus on the weekends when there is free parking
* I have students hold auditions in groups of 3, so you can potentially audition for up to 3 films in one visit (you will be asked in the Calendly signup to note all of the films and roles you would like to audition for)
* Each film is only allowed one 12-hour shoot day between March 7 - May 3, so you can potentially act in multiple films with a minimal time commitment
* All filming locations must be in or very near to Colorado Springs

COPY OF FINAL FILM AND FOOTAGE

Students are required to use their OneDrive accounts to share a copy of the finished film AND all film footage with actors by the end of the semester (I enforce this by withholding the grade on their film if they don’t provide proof that they’ve shared everything with their actors). This is a great way to get footage for your reel.

HOW TO SIGN UP FOR AUDITIONS

The following link will take you to a OneDrive folder with six audition date folders. Within each folder are the three casting calls for that date, and all three films use the same Calendly signup link (so if you are having trouble copying and pasting link from one casting call, check the other casting calls in the same folder for the link).

Casting Calls for all 18 films:

[[https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)

* The production date and audition date is listed on each casting call, as are character breakdowns. Please make sure you are available on the production date and fit the requirements of the role you are auditioning for before signing up for a time. If you have questions about individual films (including whether or not they will accept virtual auditions), please reach out to the contact email on the casting call. If you are having trouble accessing the casting calls, please DM me and I’ll get back to you ASAP.

You can view UCCS capstone films from the past few years at this link:
[https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PL15kjeIk9DclQVDGA4gQ-g-jgGcOoe8kO&si=r6PKecafpUHw6M3e](https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PL15kjeIk9DclQVDGA4gQ-g-jgGcOoe8kO&si=r6PKecafpUHw6M3e)

Thank you everyone for supporting our student filmmakers!

They know enough Japanese to teach class aboutit, but they still learn something new from their students every day. Kira's Mom (40s-50s). All Ethnicities Encouraged. Kira's mom usually very welcoming, but when you mention Kira's dad, you can see her jaw clench. Giving Kira relationship advice isn't her strong suit, but even with her cynicism she'll always lend ear to Kira. They're pretty close, even though they both lack the emotional intelligence to have deep conversations.'

I want to make this work so bad. So much blood, sweat and tears has gone into this and i'm struggling to finish this last piece of the puzzle.  Just 2 mins to either share or throw a pound our way. 

Every penny raised goes to making the film. every member of the cast & crew are here for free because they know we have something that could be massive. This is about telling a story and creating something together.

Please consider helping in anyway you can.
items.previewDescription: A powerful independent drama about fathers, sons, and the emotional cost of silence, rooted in Runcorn and told with grit and depth.

sharedPost.text:
Please help us reach our target. 🙏💙

As each day passes and we move closer to the deadline, we’re urging everyone to visit our crowdfunder and get involved. We truly want to make this film the best it can be, and having the right equipment is the way forward. 🎬✨

Everyone involved is giving their time and energy for free, driven by passion and belief in this project. Our dream is to take this film to an international audience and put Runcorn, Halton, and the North West right at the front of independent cinema. 🌍🏆

All it takes is a few quid and a share. Every single bit of support makes a real difference.

Please help us make this film the best it can be.
Made in Runcorn. By Runcorn. 💙🎥

items.text:
Looking to cast a lead role in our student film
please email r.khosssa-kulair23@lipa.ac.uk or DM betterman.lipa on instagram for more information ! 

HARRISON — Supporting Lead (Male)

Playing Age: 22–30�Accent: Neutral British (flexible)�Role Type: Charismatic / Psychological / Romantic-Thriller�Screen Time: High Supporting (appears throughout film)

Character Summary:�Harrison is magnetic, calm and intensely perceptive — the kind of person who seems to understand you before you speak. He appears in Emma’s life at her lowest moment and becomes her emotional anchor… or possibly something far more dangerous. His kindness feels genuine, but always carries an unsettling edge. The audience should never be entirely sure whether he is protector, manipulator, or both.

He rarely raises his voice. Instead, his power comes from stillness, eye contact and emotional precision. His presence shifts a room — comforting one moment, quietly threatening the next.

Performance Style:�Naturalistic and restrained. The actor must communicate subtext and tension through micro-expressions, pauses and controlled body language rather than overt emotion.

Key Traits:

* Quiet confidence

* Observant and emotionally intelligent

* Gentle but subtly possessive

* Romantic with unsettling undertones

* Ambiguous morality

Character Arc:�Begins as a mysterious stranger offering comfort, gradually embedding himself into Emma’s life. As events escalate, his protectiveness becomes increasingly intense, blurring the line between care and control. 

Script Better Man

Actor Notes:�Looking for an actor comfortable playing duality — warm and safe on the surface, but capable of conveying underlying danger without melodrama. Think: intimate psychological tension rather than overt villainy.

Comparable Tone (not impersonation):�Joe Goldberg (You), Tom Ripley, early Patrick Bateman charm without the camp

items.text:
Jeg bor i Texas nær grænsen, så jeg har smagt denne kage mange gange, men det var første gang, jeg lavede den! Utrolig. Virkelig meget nemmere, end jeg troede, den ville være, og min blev lige så lækker som de andre, jeg har smagt. Vil lave den igen!"
Må sige noget for at blive ved med at få mine opskrifter.... Tak.
Opskrift i (c.o.m.m.e.n.t).

items.text:
Hi all! I just wanted to introduce myself and share a Photo that was taken of me.

Im currently in my 4th year studying for BA (hons) in Theatre Industry Practice at Perth UHI.

Im 61 years young and have been acting/singing for around 13 years. I have played lead roles in plays, musicals and pantomimes. I am currently rehearsing for a short play called 'One Punch Kill' to raise awareness about the potential consequences of single punch assaults. I am also rehearsing for The Full Monty and Sunshine on Leith.

Once I have finished my studies I hope to source professional work in the entertainment industry.

🎬 CASTING CALL – THE GREAT LAKEVIEW BAKE-OFF 🎬
Faith-Based Family Comedy | Non-Union

WE ARE ACCEPTING EMAIL SUBMISSIONS ONLY, WE WILL NOT RESPOND TO PRIVATE MESSAGES. 

Lumiere Films is casting supporting and featured roles for our upcoming feature film shooting June 13th–20th in Clarksville, Tennessee.

Non-Union | Unpaid | Copy, Credit & Meals Provided

We are seeking the following roles:

JESENIA HERNANDEZ – Female, 16–18, Hispanic American (does not speak Spanish). Emotionally mature teen wrestling with loss and faith.

DESMOND JENKINS – Male, 30s–40s, Black. Laid-back, wise husband who speaks little but carries weight when he does.

PASTOR BROWN – Male, 40s–60s, any ethnicity. Warm, grounded church leader and peacemaker.

PERCY BELL – Male, 50s–70s, Black. Protective father, bold personality, hilarious and unfiltered.

MARIA MARTINEZ – Female, 60s–70s, Hispanic/Latina (Spanish-speaking). Loving grandmother, full of spiritual wisdom.

ERIKA – Female, 16-18, any ethnicity. Confident teen, loyal best friend with mean-girl edge.

LAUREN – Female, 30s–40s, any ethnicity. Friendly, involved church mom.

JESSICA – Female, 30s–40s, any ethnicity. Church treasurer, practical and detail-oriented.

GINA – Female, 40s–60s, White. Quiet, dependable local business owner.

OLDER WOMAN – Female, 60s–80s, any ethnicity. Bold, funny church member (1 scene).

CATALINA HERNANDEZ – Female, 30s–early 40s, Hispanic/Latina. Tony’s late wife, seen in flashbacks (no dialogue).

BOB (Voiceover) – Male, 40s–60s, any ethnicity. Tony’s boss (1 scene, voice only).

RESTAURANT HOSTESS – Female, 20s–40s, any ethnicity (1 scene).

RESTAURANT WAITER – Male or Female, 20s–40s, any ethnicity (1 scene).

⸻

📩 TO SUBMIT:

Please email lumierefilmsatl@gmail.com

Subject Line: Character Name You’re Auditioning For

Include:

• Name

• Age

• Location

• Headshots

• Resume (if applicable)

• Link to reel (if applicable)

⸻

Come be part of a heartfelt story about grief, grace, rivalry, and serving like Christ. 💛

items.text:
**SHORT FILM CASTING CALL - “TAKEAWAYS”**

**OPEN TO UNION & NON-UNION - VOLUNTEER/UNPAID**

**DIRECTOR:** Jamie Lam

**CATEGORY:** Independent Short Film - UBCP ULB

**CASTING DIRECTOR:** Cathy Huynh

**COMPENSATION:** Volunteer/Unpaid. Food provided on set. Copy of film. IMDB credit.

**FILMING DATES/LOCATION:** March 21-22, 2026 (TBC) / Vancouver, BC

**SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS:** Please email **takeawaysfilm@gmail.com** with the subject heading

**[Your Name - Role Name]** and include your headshot/photo, resume and demo reel (if applicable)

**LOGLINE:** A reluctant young boy working at his family’s restaurant learns to step up as his father quietly falls apart after his divorce.

**ANDY — Male, 10-15, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** Smart but apathetic, Andy is tired of helping out at the family restaurant, much rather preferring to play PC games at home. Even so, he takes after his dad Sam, embodying kindness and warmth when times get tough - LEAD. CANTONESE PROFICIENCY IS A PLUS.

**SAM — Male, 40-50, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** A caring and kind father, Sam owns and operates the family restaurant. His wife left him a year ago, leaving him to take care of Andy and the restaurant by himself. He grapples with being a good father while trying to manage his own grief - LEAD. MUST SPEAK FLUENT CANTONESE.

**FEMALE CUSTOMER — Female, 35-45, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** This female customers a regular at Sam’s restaurant. While paying for her food, she praises Andy for being such a well-brought up kid. 2 lines, 1 scene.

**FEMALE CUSTOMER’S DAUGHTER — Female, 5-10, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** This young girl accompanies her mother to the restaurant. No lines, 1 scene.

**LINDA — Female, 40-50, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** Linda is Sam’s ex-wife. She is seen happily walking with another man, as Sam watches sorrowfully from his restaurant’s window. No lines, 1 scene.

**YOUNG BOYS — Male, 10-15, Open ethnicity.** These young boys wave at Andy while he works at the restaurant. No lines, 1 scene.

items.text:
We're looking for **volunteer background performers **for our film, Hair or No Hair, for a dance party scene,** filming March 23 - 25th **in the Mount Pleasant area in Vancouver, BC. *Please note, we may not require all the background performers for full days.*

We strongly encourage a diverse crowd of people to submit, with a highlight on BIPOC folks. This film is Black female led, and the party is inclusive of everyone, and will showcase the Drag and Go-Go dancing scene in Vancouver.

If you are interested, please register via this link by Feb 27th:

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScq-vKacoi0WGgcIDwRc4SRY-96cdJhRLjjG_YFaij_HpIuyA/viewform

We're looking for **volunteer background performers **for our film, Hair or No Hair, for a dance party scene,** filming March 23 - 25th **in the Mount Pleasant area in Vancouver, BC. *Please note, we may not require all the background performers for full days.*

We strongly encourage a diverse crowd of people to submit, with a highlight on BIPOC folks. This film is Black female led, and the party is inclusive of everyone, and will showcase the Drag and Go-Go dancing scene in Vancouver.

If you are interested, please register via this link by Feb 27th:

I dag lavede min svigermor aftensmad med hakket oksekød, men hun skyllede det ikke. Jeg kunne ikke spise det, og jeg sørgede også for, at mine børn holdt sig væk. Jeg skyller altid hakket oksekød, inden jeg tilbereder det. Det er chokerende, at hun ikke gør det samme. Er det ikke et must?

Opskrift i kommentarerne.

items.text:
UCCS Digital Filmmaking Capstone Film Casting Call

Hello! I am looking for actors to audition for my UCCS Capstone Student Short Film. Details below:

Title: Unforced Errors

Genre: Drama

Logline: Matt is convinced his recently deceased father loved his brother more than him, but his brother Josh unknowingly feels the same way. As Matt searches for his dad’s old baseball card collection, the brothers soon discover that their father’s love was unconditional.

Roles: 

**Matt (20 – 26 years old) - Male, Any Ethnicity:**

Matt is a true younger brother. He is always trying his best to impress everyone around him and make himself noticed, but he never feels like he is good enough. He loves his brother Josh, but he has always been jealous of his relationship with their father.

 

**Josh (22 – 28 years old) - Male, Any Ethnicity:**

Josh was a high school baseball athlete, but not the jock/bully type. He has a strong exterior demeanor that hides how he truly feels: like he was never good enough for his professional baseball-playing father. While he would never want to admit it, he is jealous of his younger brother Matt and the relationship he had with their father.

Director: Zion Wilson

Producer: Onyx Riccelli

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: unforcederrorsfilm@gmail.com

Run Time: Short

Compensation: Non-Paid

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Date: Saturday, February 14th, 11am-7pm. 

Audition Location:** **UCCS Campus: El Pomar Center 103 (directions are included in the appointment confirmation).

Auditions are by appointment only. Please use the link included in the attached casting call to sign up for a time slot.

Shooting Schedule: Saturday, March 7th. Please be available for the entire day.

Project Description: UCCS Capstone Student Short Film

Please email us at unforcederrorsfilm@gmail.com if you have any questions. Thank you!
